-- Hong Kong drawndown mortgage loans rise 2.3 pct in May from April
-- By Christina Lo and Twinnie Siu
-- Fri Jun 27, 2014 05:48AM EDT
-- None



June 27 (Reuters) - New mortgage loans drawn down in Hong Kong totalled HK$16.3 billion ($2.10 billion) in May, up 2.3 percent from a month earlier, Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) data showed on Friday.

